-- Russian assets lower after Putin orders food import restrictions
-- 
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 02:08AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Aug 7 (Reuters) - Russian assets fell in early trade on Thursday after President Vladimir Putin ordered food import restrictions on countries which have imposed sanctions on Russia over the Ukraine crisis.

At 0605 GMT, the dollar-denominated RTS index <.IRTS> was down 0.5 percent at 1,155 points, while its rouble-based peer MICEX <.MCX> traded 0.4 percent lower at 1,329 points.